{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T14:08:48.856Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Permission modes control how much Claude Code is allowed to do "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"without"},{"type":"text","text":" asking you first, from “ask before everything” through “read‑only planner” all the way to “no safety net, run everything.”"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Permission Modes Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every time Claude wants to use a tool — read or edit a file, run a shell command, call an MCP server, hit the network, etc. — the request goes through a permission gate. The active "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"permission mode"},{"type":"text","text":" tells that gate when to prompt you, when to auto‑approve, and when to refuse the action outright."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This sits on top of the allow/deny rules configured in settings and project files: the mode defines the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"baseline behavior"},{"type":"text","text":", while allow/deny rules provide fine‑grained overrides."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Modes in Claude Code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Different sources list slightly different counts, but the same core modes appear across the official docs and teaching material. At a high level you can think of five canonical modes:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Typical flag / name"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it does"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Primary use case"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--permission-mode default"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompts for every sensitive action unless pre‑allowed"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everyday development on unfamiliar codebases"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"acceptEdits"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--permission-mode acceptEdits"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto‑approves file edits and safe FS ops; still prompts for shell and high‑risk tools"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Focused coding when you mostly trust the context"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"plan"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--permission-mode plan"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Read‑only: Claude can analyze and propose plans, but does not execute tools"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture, reviews, dry‑runs"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"autoApprove / auto"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--permission-mode autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":" or “auto classifier mode”"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto‑approves (almost) all tools based on internal heuristics; minimal prompts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CI containers, scripted workflows, experiments"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bypass / dangerously‑skip‑permissions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--dangerously-skip-permissions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Disables the permission gate and runs tools without checks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Highly isolated sandboxes only, never on real machines"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"On the interactive TUI/CLI, you can cycle among the main interactive modes (typically "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default → acceptEdits → plan"},{"type":"text","text":") with a single keybinding (often Shift+Tab), so changing the level of autonomy is a constant‑time operation during a session."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How the Permission Gate Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Regardless of mode, every tool call follows the same general flow:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude decides it wants to use a tool"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For example: “Run "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":"”, “Edit "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"src/app.ts"},{"type":"text","text":"”, or “Call MCP server X”."}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Permission gate evaluates rules"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before touching your filesystem, shell, or network, the call is checked against deny rules, allow rules, and the current permission mode."}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deny rules are checked first"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If the command or tool matches a deny pattern, the call is refused outright, regardless of the mode or allow rules."}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow rules then bypass prompts"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If it matches an allow rule and wasn’t denied, the call is auto‑approved with no interactive prompt."}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mode decides what to do for the rest"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":", anything not pre‑allowed triggers an interactive prompt. - In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":", file edits and safe FS ops are auto‑approved; shell and risky tools still prompt. - In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"plan"},{"type":"text","text":", tools are never actually executed; Claude reports what it "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"would"},{"type":"text","text":" do instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This layered design is why the “real” way to reduce prompt fatigue is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" to jump straight to Bypass, but to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default mode + a well‑tuned allow list + targeted deny rules"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode-by-Mode Behavior and When to Use Each"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" mode"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In default mode, Claude Code prompts for every tool invocation that isn’t explicitly allowed by an allow rule."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before editing a file, it asks."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before running a shell command, it asks."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before touching anything outside the project directory, it asks."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Working on unfamiliar or critical codebases."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learning how Claude behaves on a new project."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team environments where explicit approvals are required."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Typical workflow:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start in default mode."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As repetitive, safe actions appear (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"go test./..."},{"type":"text","text":", editing under "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"src/"},{"type":"text","text":"), use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/permissions"},{"type":"text","text":" or your settings file to add allow rules so those actions run without prompts."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":" mode"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"AcceptEdits is designed for hands‑on coding sessions where file edits are common and shell commands are rarer."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In this mode, Claude:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto‑approves file edits and common filesystem ops ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"mkdir"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"mv"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"cp"},{"type":"text","text":", etc.) inside the project and any additional directories you’ve configured."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still prompts for shell commands and riskier tools unless covered by allow rules."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Focused refactoring or feature work in a mostly understood codebase."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High‑frequency “edit this file, re‑run tests occasionally” workflows, where prompts for every edit would be too noisy."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade‑off:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You get smoother coding with fewer interruptions but rely more heavily on deny rules and shell allowlists for safety around command execution."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"plan"},{"type":"text","text":" mode (read‑only)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan mode turns Claude into a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"read‑only architect"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude can explore files, index the project, and propose a detailed step‑by‑step plan of edits and commands."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It does "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" execute those edits or commands; instead, it describes what it "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"would"},{"type":"text","text":" do if given permission."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architectural reviews and “what would you do?” analyses."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety‑critical situations where you want a plan to inspect before any change."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Teaching scenarios: use plan mode to generate a patch, inspect it, then apply it manually or by switching modes."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Typical pattern:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"plan"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask Claude to design a refactor or migration; it produces a plan and proposed edits."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Once satisfied, switch to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":" and let it execute the plan with normal prompts and protections."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":" / classifier “auto” mode"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Some guides describe an “auto” or “autoApprove” mode where a classifier or heuristic decides when to skip prompts."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The gate still exists, but prompts are minimized based on risk assessment."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More actions are auto‑approved, especially in well‑scoped projects and CI‑like contexts."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deny rules remain hard stops; they still override everything."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In containerized or ephemeral environments where rollback is trivial."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For scripted, repeatable tasks where interactive prompts hurt automation."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For experimentation with a clear fallback (e.g., git reset, disposable branches)."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This mode should usually be combined with strict deny rules to enforce boundaries around destructive commands ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"rm -rf"},{"type":"text","text":", database resets, production deploys, etc.)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"bypassPermissions"},{"type":"text","text":" / "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--dangerously-skip-permissions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"At the far end of the spectrum is the “no guardrails” mode — often exposed as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--dangerously-skip-permissions"},{"type":"text","text":" or a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"bypassPermissions"},{"type":"text","text":" setting."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The permission gate is effectively disabled."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tool calls run as if they were pre‑approved, subject only to external sandboxing or OS‑level permissions."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is explicitly marked as dangerous in official guidance and community tools."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use (if ever):"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Only in tightly sandboxed environments (e.g., throwaway containers with no real credentials, ephemeral CI runners with read‑only fixtures)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Never on a developer laptop or any environment that can touch production or personal data."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Most “expert usage” material emphasizes that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bypass is almost never the right solution to prompt fatigue"},{"type":"text","text":"; the right pattern is default mode plus allow/deny rules."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Permission Modes vs Allow/Deny Rules"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Permission modes are only one part of the security model. A robust configuration combines them with data‑driven rules:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow list"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Patterns for tools and commands that may run without asking. - Used to auto‑approve safe operations and reduce prompts."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deny list"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Patterns for tools and commands that must "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"never"},{"type":"text","text":" run. - Deny entries override allow entries when both match (deny wins)."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mode"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Defines what happens for everything else. - Default: ask. AcceptEdits: auto‑approve edits. Plan: never execute. Auto/Bypass: minimal or no prompts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The usual “expert” setup ends up being:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mode"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow rules"},{"type":"text","text":": common safe commands ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pytest"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"docker compose up"},{"type":"text","text":" against local services) and directory‑scoped tool use."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deny rules"},{"type":"text","text":": destructive or high‑risk commands ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"rm -rf"},{"type":"text","text":", production deploys, migrations against prod DB, system‑level commands)."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Permission modes define "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"how often Claude must ask you"},{"type":"text","text":" before taking actions, from fully interactive to fully autonomous."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Default, AcceptEdits, and Plan form the main “interactive” cycle for day‑to‑day work; Auto and Bypass are specialized modes for automation and heavily sandboxed environments."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every tool call flows through the same gate: deny rules → allow rules → mode‑dependent prompt or execution."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deny rules always win over allow rules, giving you a way to define “never do this” constraints, regardless of mode."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The recommended practice for most workflows is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"default mode plus well‑tuned allow/deny rules"},{"type":"text","text":", not bypassing permissions entirely."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
